  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tangy-tomato-and-goats-cheese-linguine/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a medium-sized pot with a large drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Allow them to sizzle in the oil for 30 secs</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tangy-tomato-and-goats-cheese-linguine/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>and<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong>, then increase the heat to medium and stir</p><p>Cook for 10-15 min until the tomatoes have reduced to the consistency of a thick sauce – this is your<strong> tomato sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tangy-tomato-and-goats-cheese-linguine/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>linguine</strong> to a large pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a big pinch of <strong>salt </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Bring to the boil and cook for 7-9 min, or until cooked with a slight bite</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tangy-tomato-and-goats-cheese-linguine/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and chop roughly</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tangy-tomato-and-goats-cheese-linguine/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped spinach</strong> to the <strong>linguine</strong></p><p>Cook for 30 secs until the <strong>spinach</strong> has wilted, then drain the lot and return to the pot</p><p>Once the tomato<strong> </strong>sauce has thickened, add your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tangy-tomato-and-goats-cheese-linguine/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the tomato<strong> </strong>sauce from the heat and stir in <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>goats' cheese</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato & goats' cheese sauce</strong></p><p>Sprinkle your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame seeds </strong>and <strong>black sesame seeds</strong> onto a chopping board and roll the<strong> remaining goats' cheese </strong>in the seeds to coat and reserve for garnish</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tangy-tomato-and-goats-cheese-linguine/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> linguine & spinach</strong> to the tomato & goats' cheese sauce and mix until the linguine is coated – this is your <strong>tangy tomato & goats' cheese linguine</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>tangy tomato & goats' cheese linguine</strong> with the <strong>seeded</strong> <strong>goats' cheese</strong> crumbled on top</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
